<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<section xml:id="section-2" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Including Interactive Graphics</title>
  <p>In this section, we will see an example 
    of a graph created using GeoGebra.</p>

  
<figure width="50%">
 <interactive geogebra="rqrxy7j9" shift-drag-zoom="yes"/>
<caption>Use the slider to observe that when <m>h\to 0</m>, the vector 
  <m>\frac{\vec{r}(t_0+h)-\vec{r}(t_0)}{h}</m> becomes parallel to the tangent line.</caption>
</figure>


</section>
